<br>
When you see your guild master be sure to put at LEAST one training point into each skill you want to raise.<br>
<br>
Since you get 5 skill points per level you should have about 20 now.<br>
<br>
Put one into peircing (for your dagger)<br>
and one each into your spell casting abilities (abejuation, alteration, cahnnelling, conjuration, divination, and evocation)<br>
and now that you are level 4 put a point into meditate (it helps you regain mana faster when you sit and look at your spell book while regenerating)<br>
<br>
It's important to put at least one point in because your skill in those areas won't increase until there is apoitn allocated to them. And don't worrk, those skill will raise up on thier own as you fight and cast spells.<br>
<br>
You can then spread the rest of the points out in things you want to work on or just save them up for later use.<br>
<br>
Here is a list of skills and at what level they are available to you:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://eq.crgaming.com/creationguides/skills/default.asp?class=Magician">eq.crgaming.com/creationg...s=Magician</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
And remember, each time you gain a level (or DING! as we call it) you get five more training points. <p><p>&nbsp;<p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474342"><img src="http://www.inktank.com/images/eZsig.gif" height=150 width=508 border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrighter2>Dabrighter2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 52<br> <font color=#333333>(1/3/03 9:18:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UGH!  I am so confused...</span><hr size=1> I would like to also recommend <br>
