<br>
So a discussion might go like this:<br>
<br>
You: &quot;Hail NPC person&quot;<br>
NPC: &quot;Hail Dracca. I am sorry, but I'm not too talkative. I'm worried about my [son].&quot;<br>
You: &quot;What about your son?&quot;<br>
NPC: &quot;He was capruted by [orcs] and taken to the slave pits.&quot;<br>
You: &quot;What orcs?&quot;<br>
<br>
And so on from there.<br>
<br>
Typically I find the best thing to do is to go to Allakazam and search for quests by zone since there are SOOO many quests and not all of them will be for your race class combination. Some quests are for Enchanters only or for Dwarves or so forth.<br>
<br>
But typically quests given in your guild hall will send you on your way for some quests that you can do and get rewarded for. <p><p>&nbsp;<p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=474342"><img src="http://www.inktank.com/images/eZsig.gif" height=150 width=508 border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=feninie>Feninie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#333333>(1/4/03 12:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthelibrary.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=31.topic&index=29>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: UGH!  I am so confused...</span><hr size=1> And on the subject of flare.<br>
<br>
It's not totally useless, just mostly useless.  Not only does it have a pretty light, it effects your stamina loss.<br>
<br>
Been ages since I used it, but if it is a duration buff, then stamina loss is reduced while it is active. I doubt stamina is an issue for you however.<br>
